result.execSummary:
The defendant Dana T. Slater was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Misappropriate ID Info - Avoid Penalty, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.201(2)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

parties.name: Clark County Clerk of Circuit Court

supervisions.notes:
Sentence is imposed and stayed, if imposed sentence is to run consecutive to imposed sentence in 15CF38. Defendant was found to be eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.
Consecutive to: Imposed sentences in 15CF96& 15CF38 to run consecutive to each other.
Conditions of Extended Supervision are the same as those of the underlying probation in this case.

The defendant shall pay Department of Correction fees as directed by the agent.  Defendant was ordered to report upon release to the probation and parole office. 15CM219 Cts 1-4 were dismissed and read-in to this case.
Probation in 15CF38 & 15CF96 to run concurrent to each other.

miscConds.notes:
Fine and/or costs to be paid on a schedule established by the agent.  
Defendant is ordered to pay the DNA surcharge, and to make arrangements to provide a DNA sample, within 48 hours, for testing through the Clark County Sheriff Department or if on probation, to the Department of Corrections as is required in all felony convictions.
Defendant shall attend counseling, treatments, programming, evaluations as deemed appropriate by the agent releasing all records to the agent upon request

Defendant shall not possess or consume any alcohol, and not go into places that sell alcohol except incidentally such as a grocery store, convenience store or gas station or other such place where alcohol is not sold for consumption on the premises.  

Defendant shall not possess or consume any medication or drug except as may be specifically prescribed by a medical professional for defendant, and then shall be taken only as prescribed.  

Defendant is not to drive any motorized vehicle: (a) unless defendant is in possession of a valid Wisconsin operator's license for the type of motor vehicle being driven; (b) defendant and such motor vehicle are insured as required by law; and (c) defendant is in possession of valid proof of insurance while operating the motor vehicle.  

The defendant shall have no contact with Katheryn C Hulett  of any kind, whether direct or indirect, including in person, in writing, by phone, by e-mail or other electronic means, through a third party or in any other way.

timeConds.notes: Defendant to receive credit for 146 days served.
